.NAME
       zappy_server - generate the inhabitantsâ€™ world

.SYNOPSIS
       zappy_server [OPTIONS]

.DESCRIPTION
       zappy_server generates a world for inhabitants to live in and interact.

.OPTIONS
       -p, --port PORT
              Specifies the port number on which the server listens.

       -x, --width WIDTH
              Specifies the width of the world.

       -y, --height HEIGHT
              Specifies the height of the world.

       -n, --name TEAM_NAMES
              Specifies the names of the teams. Multiple team names should be separated by spaces.

       -c, --clients CLIENTS_NUMBER
              Specifies the number of authorized clients per team.

       -f, --freq FREQUENCY
              Specifies the reciprocal of the time unit for the execution of actions.

.USAGE
       Example usage:

              ./zappy_server -p 4242 -x 100 -y 100 -n team1 team2 -c 10 -f 100

